This paper is about a clinical natural language processing (cNLP) annotation system, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves usability testing and user experience evaluation, which could be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY). The use of machine learning and ensemble pipelines in the system could also relate to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
